FT  02 JUN 94 / D-day communications systems set in place
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Broadcast signalling equipment is set up near the Normandy beaches for the
D-day 50th anniversary commemoration between June 1 and June 6. British
Telecommunications will transmit coverage to broadcasters from countries
including the UK, US and Canada. Five BT satellite trucks positioned along
the coastline will beam signals to a media centre in Portsmouth.
