<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUN 94 / Construction groups to lobby with one voice
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR, Construction Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The formation of a powerful trade association to act as a single voice in
Whitehall and Brussels for a large part of the UK construction industry was
announced yesterday.
The move is in line with a drive by Mr Michael Heseltine, trade and industry
secretary, to reduce the number of trade associations with access to civil
servants and ministers by restricting contact to a smaller number of 'lead
asso-ciations'.
The establishment of an umbrella body to represent the industry was
supported by two of its largest employer organisations, the Building
Employers Confederation and the Federation of Civil Engineering Employers,
and by Major Construction Groups, which represents 11 of the country's
largest contractors.
It is hoped that other trade organisations and professional bodies will
eventually support the initiative.
The sector, with sales of about Pounds 50bn a year, is one of Britain
biggest industries, contributing up to a tenth of gross domestic product.
It is represented by several lobby groups which look after the diverse
interests of quantity surveyors, architects, building-material producers and
large international contractors.
This has led to duplication of effort and in some cases has caused confusion
among ministers and civil servants who have been listening to conflicting
messages.
The new body - given the working title Newco - will be expected to provide a
focal voice for the industry's lobbying efforts and to lead industry
thinking on strategic issues.
It will continue to recognise the independence of member organisations such
as the BEC and FCEC.
PA Consulting Group has been appointed to draw up a series of aims and
objectives for the trade association. Its report is due by late summer 'with
the intention of establishing the new organisation before the end of the
year'.
Mr Heseltine has said that where lead trade associations emerged he would
expect officials to 'refer to me only proposals from that lead association'.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
