<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUN 94 / Crest wins excess of financial support
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Bank of England said yesterday there had been substantial
oversubscription by institutions committed to supporting its proposed Crest
paperless share settlement system.
It said 74 firms and institutions had expressed willingness to be
shareholders by the end of May, the closing date for subscriptions to raise
the Pounds 12m for the 'building' phase of Crest, which is due to be
completed by the end of next year.
Commitments will be scaled back pro rata in accordance with the four tiers
of support, from Pounds 375,000 for those in tier 1 to Pounds 30,000 for
those in tier 4.
Crestco, a new company, will be formed by October using the share
subscriptions.
It will own and run Crest, while the Bank will build the core system and
provide legal and business support - for fees of Pounds 10m - until the end
of next year.
The prospective shareholders include 21 of the 28 marketmakers, 28 firms
specialising in retail broking and a number of custodians, payment providers
and institutional fund managers.
</TEXT>
