FT  02 JUN 94 / Pledge on NHS cash planned
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government is expected to announce today that it is providing an
additional Pounds 2m to pay for part-time consultant posts in the National
Health Service.
Baroness Cumberlege, junior health minister, will tell a Royal College of
Physicians conference that she believes doctors want a more flexible career
pattern, and that bringing up children and developing other talents are also
part of a doctor's life.
The Royal College of Physicians says in a report published yesterday that
the needs of doctors who want part-time specialist posts are not being met
and that if the system does not change the NHS will be deprived of skilled
staff.
