FT  01 JUN 94 / London Stock Exchange: De La Rue rises
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Printing group De La Rue was one of the few shades of blue on dealers'
screens in early trading after turning in a solid set of full-year results.
Underlying profits jumped 20 per cent to Pounds 123.3m, with analysts moving
their forecasts for the current year by around 8 per cent to a range of
Pounds 133m to 140m. The shares strengthened to close 16 up at 859p on 1.5m
traded.
Speculation over how the company intends to spend its cash pile,
particularly in the wake of the failed talks with Portals, was prominent
among dealers, although they added that criticism over De La Rue's handling
of the affair had adversely affected City opinion. Portals' shares continued
to suffer from the fallout of the aborted merger talks, dropping a further
10 to 643p.
