deals
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Northern Telecom of Canada has signed contracts worth about USDollars 82m to
supply advanced telecommunications switching systems to three Chinese
provincial governments, Reuter reports from New York.
The company said it will install 13 switching systems for the Tianjin Posts
and Telecommunications Administration, worth Dollars 40m, and in Shaanxi
Province, nine switching systems worth more than Dollars 22m. The company is
also installing systems for the Hebei Posts and Telecommunications
Administration, worth Dollars 20.6m.
Northern Telecom said the 37 digital multiplexing systems can each support
up to 100,000 telephone lines.
