FT  01 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Rackwood ahead of forecast
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Rackwood Mineral Holdings, the opencast mining group which obtained a
listing in January, returned pre-tax profits of Pounds 29,000 for 1993.
That compared with a prospectus forecast of Pounds 10,000 and was achieved
on turnover of Pounds 2.97m. Interest charges accounted for Pounds 221,000.
Basic earnings per share emerged at 0.36p; on a pro forma basis the figure
was 0.18p.
The shares, placed at 40p in January, rose 2p to 48p.
