<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Stratagem turns in Pounds 280,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Stratagem, which has evolved from an investment company into a group with
interests in the manufacturing, distribution and service sectors, yesterday
reported a pre-tax profit of Pounds 280,000 for the six months to
end-February.
The outcome compared with profits of Pounds 272,000 and came from turnover
up from Pounds 690,000 to Pounds 33.8m. The results were bolstered by the
inclusion of a first-time contribution from Harrison Industries, acquired
last August.
The directors said that all three divisions acquired with Harrison were
reporting profits by the end of the period.
At the same time Veritas, the car dealership operation, had benefited from
the reorganisation which was implemented after it became wholly owned in
late-November 1993.
Earnings per share emerged at 1.6p (2.2p) and the interim dividend is
maintained at 1.5p.
</TEXT>
