<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUN 94 / Office scheme for Birmingham
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Richardson Barberry Properties is planning the biggest speculative office
building in the central business area of Birmingham since before the
recession.
The company is a joint venture between the Richardson brothers, the Black
Country property developers who built the Merry Hill shopping centre in
Dudley, and Barberry Properties of Stourbridge. It said yesterday that it
had lodged a planning application with Birmingham City Council.
The 22-storey building will have 200,000 sq ft of offices and will cost
Pounds 75m. It is next to a similar unit by the same company which is
intended for the Lord Chancellor's Department and Coopers &amp; Lybrand, the
accountancy firm.
