FT  01 JUN 94 / NZ budget goes into surplus
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Bill Birch, New Zealand finance minister, said yesterday the country
would show a budget surplus of NZDollars 420m (Pounds 163m) for the year to
June 30, the first surplus for 17 years, writes Terry Hall in Wellington.
This is a sharp turnaround from the Treasury prediction last October before
the general election that returned the National party government. The
Treasury then predicted a deficit of NZDollars 1.4bn. Mr Birch said that
thanks to the rapidly improving economy, tax receipts would be NZDollars 2bn
higher than expected, while government spending and other costs had been
held down.
