FT  01 JUN 94 / Taiwan budget trimmed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan's legislature has trimmed the government's proposed 1994-95 budget by
2.15 per cent, including a cut of Dollars 203.7m (Pounds 135.8m) in defence
spending, AP reports from Taipei.
Defence spending will none the less take 24.5 per cent of the total, up from
23 per cent in 1994.
