<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: Canada slightly easier in search for
direction
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Toronto stocks finished a lethargic session slightly lower after the market
had searched in vain for direction.
The TSE 300 composite index slipped 8.2 to 4,320.7 and declining issues
outscored advances by 353 to 283. Volume dropped to a mere 26.1m shares from
Friday's 60.9m and trading value was down to CDollars 209.8m from CDollars
636.7m, reflecting the holiday closures of the US and UK markets yesterday.
Inco, off CDollars 1 1/8 at CDollars 35 5/8 , said the company and the union
representing its hourly-paid Ontario employees have reached a tentative
agreement for a new three-year contract.
Aber Resources jumped CDollars 2, or 37 per cent, to CDollars 7 3/8 as it
reported good initial results from a diamond discovery in the arctic.
