<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: Istanbul drops 6.9% on bonds
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Turkish equities remained under pressure from the bond market on news of
another forthcoming treasury bill auction. The composite index fell
1,087.75, or 6.9 per cent, to 14,737.37, with most shares finishing limit
down.
Among the actives, Eregli weakened TL300 to TL4,050 as overall turnover
remained static at TL894.6bn.
Tel Aviv lost some of its gains on profit-taking after two sessions of
rising share prices.
The Mishtanim index closed 4.52, or 2.3 per cent, down at 194.82 following
an advance of 3.5 per cent on Sunday, when dealers were already becoming
pessimistic again.
Traders said that portfolio managers, anxious to realise profits in a
nervous market, dumped shares selectively.
