FT  31 MAY 94 / International Company News: LOT
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Polish government plans to sell 49 per cent of LOT, the country's
national airline, Mr Boguslaw Liberadzki, transport minister, said
yesterday, AP-DJ reports from Warsaw. The government was not looking
specifically for another airline or a single investor, the minister said.
